features: High performance DDR4 memory illuminates your system with vivid, animated lighting from ten ultra-bright, individually addressable RGB LEDs per module.
Take control with CORSAIR iCUE software and synchronize lighting across all your CORSAIR iCUE compatible products, including memory, fans, coolers, keyboards and more.
Customize lighting profiles with millions of different patterns and colors, or create your own in CORSAIR iCUE software.
Compatible with Intel and AMD DDR4 motherboards.
Requires no extra wires or cables for a clean and seamless install.
Custom performance PCB for the highest signal quality and performance stability.
Carefully screened ICs for extended overclocking potential.
Built-in aluminum heat spreader provides superb memory cooling even when overclocked.
Supports Intel XMP 2.0 for simple one-setting installation and optimum performance.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works and looks great! Runs fine at 3200 mhz on MSI Z490-A Pro motherboard.
reviews.reviewText: I knew going in that I would probably not be able to run this at the 3600 mhz that it was rated to work at, when I installed it on my setup. I am currently running a Corsair Vengeance computer with an i7 11700 non k cpu, and a MSI Z490-A pro motherboard.Once installed and set to XMP it gave me the overclock error. I dropped it to 3200 mhz and it booted fine with no problems since. I am running bios E7C751Z1.2CB, or 2.CB is how CPU Z reads it.It should easily go higher, but I will have to play with the overclock settings and see how high I can get it to work while being stable. This kit is using Nanya chips, at least the sticks I have, which is fine.Even if it goes no higher, it has been a good upgrade from 16 gb. Things seem to run very smoothly and I have no problems running discord and surfing the web on my second monitor, while gaming on my main one. I have two 27" MSI monitors side by side.The rgb looks great, and since I have a Corsair Vengeance computer already it just worked right off the bat with my icue software.I feel much better about having 32 gbs of memory for my future PC games. I also know that, although I have no plans too, in the future if I upgrade or change the motherboard and possibly the cpu, I can still use this memory and it will work fine at its rated speed of 3600 mhz.I have no cons. Corsair makes great memory and other computer components, and this memory was a great value at this low of a price in the summer of 2023.

These are massive though, so if you don't have a lot of room, maybe look for something else (see picture comparing to old RAM).While the physical sticks are great, I did take 1 star because I am not a fan of their software, iCUE, for lighting. I recently acquired the CORSAIR Vengeance RGB PRO 32GB (2x16GB) DDR4 3600 (PC4-28800) C18 Desktop Memory to pair with i5-13600K and 4080 FE, and I must say it has been an excellent addition to my PC setup. In this review, I will share my experience with this memory kit, focusing on its performance, aesthetics, and overall value.Performance:The CORSAIR Vengeance RGB PRO memory kit boasts impressive performance specifications. With a speed of DDR4 3600 and a CAS latency of 18, it delivers fast and responsive performance for demanding tasks. I noticed a significant improvement in overall system responsiveness, particularly when running resource-intensive applications and multitasking. The increased memory capacity of 32GB ensures smooth performance and effortless multitasking, even when dealing with large files or running memory-intensive software.Aesthetics:The standout feature of the CORSAIR Vengeance RGB PRO memory kit is its stunning RGB lighting. The individually addressable RGB LEDs on each module can be customized using the CORSAIR iCUE software, allowing for a wide range of lighting effects and color combinations. The lighting synchronization with other compatible CORSAIR products further enhances the overall aesthetic appeal, creating an immersive and visually striking setup. The sleek, low-profile design of the modules adds to their visual appeal and compatibility with most CPU coolers.Build Quality and Durability:CORSAIR is well-known for its high-quality components, and the Vengeance RGB PRO memory kit lives up to that reputation. The modules are built with precision and attention to detail, ensuring long-lasting durability. The aluminum heat spreaders not only enhance the aesthetics but also contribute to effective heat dissipation, allowing for stable performance even during extended use. The sturdy construction of the modules provides confidence in their reliability.Easy Installation and Compatibility:Installing the CORSAIR Vengeance RGB PRO memory kit was a breeze. The modules fit seamlessly into my motherboard's DIMM slots, and the XMP 2.0 support made it easy to set up and optimize the memory settings for maximum performance. The compatibility with a wide range of motherboards ensures that most users can benefit from this memory kit without any compatibility concerns.Value:While the CORSAIR Vengeance RGB PRO memory kit falls in the higher price range, it offers excellent value for enthusiasts and gamers seeking high-performance memory with captivating RGB lighting. The combination of impressive performance, eye-catching aesthetics, and reliable build quality justifies the investment for those who prioritize both style and functionality in their PC setup.Final Thoughts:The CORSAIR Vengeance RGB PRO 32GB (2x16GB) DDR4 3600 (PC4-28800) C18 Desktop Memory is a top-notch memory kit that delivers not only exceptional performance but also adds a touch of RGB brilliance to your PC build. With its impressive speed, ample capacity, customizable RGB lighting, and reliable build quality, this memory kit is a worthy upgrade for users looking to enhance their PC's performance and aesthetics.Disclaimer: I purchased the CORSAIR Vengeance RGB PRO 32GB DDR4 3600 Desktop Memory independently and did not receive it as part of any specific program or incentive. My review is solely based on my personal experience and observations with this memory kit.
